# Hackathon Todo - Console Application

A console application for managing todo tasks, built as part of the "Evolution of Todo - Hackathon II" project.

## Features

- Add new tasks with title and optional description
- View all tasks in a formatted table
- Update existing tasks
- Delete tasks
- Mark tasks as complete/incomplete

## Prerequisites

- Python 3.13 or higher
- UV package manager

## Installation

1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone <repository-url>
   cd hackathon-todo
   ```

2. Install dependencies using UV:
   ```bash
   uv sync --all-extras
   ```

3. Install the package in development mode:
   ```bash
   uv build
   uv install -e .
   ```

## Usage

The application provides a command-line interface with the following commands:

### Add a Task
```bash
todo-cli add --title "Task Title" --description "Task Description"
```

### List All Tasks
```bash
todo-cli list
```

### View a Specific Task
```bash
todo-cli view <task-id>
```

### Update a Task
```bash
todo-cli update <task-id> --title "New Title" --description "New Description"
```

### Delete a Task
```bash
todo-cli delete <task-id>
```

### Mark a Task as Complete
```bash
todo-cli complete <task-id>
```

### Mark a Task as Incomplete
```bash
todo-cli uncomplete <task-id>
```

